    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Right Decision</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bill Teer letter comments on May 23 article on deciding on a treatment for prostate cancer</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As one who had to make the same prostate cancer decision last year as Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani, I know exactly what he is experiencing (''No Easy Decisions for a Man of Decision,'' May 23). I chose surgery as the best for me. But if I had a twin brother, he might make a different decision.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As one who had to make the same prostate cancer decision last year as Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani, I know exactly what he is experiencing (''No Easy Decisions for a Man of Decision,'' May 23). I chose surgery as the best for me. But if I had a twin brother, he might make a different decision.</p>
        <p>As mentioned, incontinence is a possible complications. During this phase, I kept my sense of humor by thinking that it was an advantage to be six decades old instead of six months old: you can change your own diaper.</p>
        <p>BILL TEER  Washington</p>
      </block>
